      'One of the DuckDuckGo Privacy Browser\\\'s most appealing features, especially on mobile, is the "Fire Button." With a single tap, it instantly clears all your tabs, browsing data, and cookies, giving you a fresh start. This is incredibly useful for maintaining ephemeral browsing sessions. While it excels on mobile, DuckDuckGo has also released a beta desktop version that integrates similar features. However, as it\\\'s still in earlier stages on desktop, it offers less advanced customization and extension support compared to Firefox or Brave. Its privacy policy is excellent, emphasizing data minimization and transparent practices. Like Mozilla, DuckDuckGo is based in the US, but their business model is built around non-tracking ads on their search engine, not selling browsing data.',
      '**Verdict:** The DuckDuckGo Privacy Browser is a fantastic option for mobile users who want simple, effective, and intuitive privacy protection without configuration hassle. For desktop, it\\\'s a promising newcomer but currently less feature-rich than its competitors. All versions are free. I give it a \'Recommended for mobile-first privacy and ease of use\'.'
